description:
First light with my ASI183MM-Pro and all I have to say is this camera is awesome! The details this camera yields are impressive! Very happy with it.

Target: NGC 7000 - North America Nebula / Cygnus wall area

Gear:
Camera: ASI1600MM w/ EAF, EFW
Filters: Astrodon 5nm Ha, 3nm SII, OIII
Scope: Meade 70mm Quad APO 350mm FL f/5
Guidescope: Williams Optics 30mm Uniguide
Guidecam: ASI120MM mini
Mount: SW EQ6R Pro
Pegasus Astro Pocket Power Box
Astro-Zap dew heaters

Image details:
25x300s HA, Gain 139, -15c
25x300s OIII, Gain 139, -15c
20x300s SII, Gain 139, -15c
25 darks, flats, darkflats
6 hrs total
Bortle 5/6 sky

Acquisition/Edits:
SharpCap, NINA, PHD2, Stellarium, Pixinsight, Photoshop
For more of my images, find me on Instagram here: https://www.instagram.com/colorado_astro/
imaging_cameras: ZWO ASI OIptical ZWO ASI 183 MM PRO
title: NGC 7000 - North America Nebula
